1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commemorate the fortieth anniversary of Entergy's River Bend Station and to recognize
3 the important role nuclear power plays in providing safe and reliable electricity to
4 Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, Entergy's River Bend Station has proudly served the residents of West
6 Feliciana Parish, the state of Louisiana, and the Gulf Coast region for forty years and
7 provided safe, reliable, and carbon-free electricity since commencing commercial operation
8 in 1986; and
9 WHEREAS, River Bend Station is a cornerstone of energy resilience in Southeast
10 Louisiana, and it plays a vital role in meeting the power needs of nearly half a million
11 customers by providing a maximum dependable capacity of nine hundred seventy-eight
12 megawatts, and contributing to grid stability during periods of peak demand and extreme
13 weather events; and
14 WHEREAS, River Bend Station has more than eight hundred employees and
15 contractors who have demonstrated a commitment to operational excellence, nuclear safety,
16 emergency preparedness, and professional standards; these persons exemplify the spirit of
17 public service and technical leadership; and
18 WHEREAS, River Bend Station maintains a strong and ongoing partnership with the
19 West Feliciana, East Feliciana, Pointe Coupee, and East Baton Rouge communities by
20 providing local jobs, supporting charitable organizations, investing in STEM education, and
21 preparing future generations through workforce development initiatives; and
